COMPATIBILITY RATE → 1/e
======================================================================

  1/e = 0.3678794412

  n=3: rate = 0.5000000000, error = +1.32e-01
  n=4: rate = 0.4583333333, error = +9.05e-02
  n=5: rate = 0.4416666667, error = +7.38e-02
  n=6: rate = 0.4291666667, error = +6.13e-02
  n=7: rate = 0.4204365079, error = +5.26e-02
  n=8: rate = 0.4138640873, error = +4.60e-02
  n=9: rate = 0.4087549603, error = +4.09e-02
  n=10: rate = 0.4046673832, error = +3.68e-02
  n=11: rate = 0.4013230269, error = +3.34e-02
  n=12: rate = 0.3985360613, error = +3.07e-02
  n=13: rate = 0.3961778597, error = +2.83e-02
  n=14: rate = 0.3941565441, error = +2.63e-02

  THEOREM: The fraction of ordered pairs (π, σ) of permutations
  of [n] such that the Hamiltonian path orderings π and σ are
  compatible (no edge in opposite directions) equals
  A000255(n-1)/n! → 1/e as n → ∞.

======================================================================
CV² SEQUENCE AND 1/4 LIMIT CONJECTURE
======================================================================

  CV² = Var(H)/E[H]² sequence:
    n=3: CV² = 1/3 = 0.3333333333, CV²-1/4 = 1/12 = 0.0833333333
    n=4: CV² = 1/3 = 0.3333333333, CV²-1/4 = 1/12 = 0.0833333333
    n=5: CV² = 19/60 = 0.3166666667, CV²-1/4 = 1/15 = 0.0666666667
    n=6: CV² = 13/45 = 0.2888888889, CV²-1/4 = 7/180 = 0.0388888889
    n=7: CV² = 131/504 = 0.2599206349, CV²-1/4 = 5/504 = 0.0099206349

  The sequence CV²-1/4 → 0:
    n=5: 1/15 ≈ 0.066667
    n=6: 7/180 ≈ 0.038889
    n=7: 5/504 ≈ 0.009921

  (CV²-1/4) × n! gives integers/2:
    n=3: 1/2
    n=4: 2
    n=5: 8
    n=6: 28
    n=7: 50

